 surprise. The store turned out to be a hairdresser's, and a ladies' one at that. Luzhin, looking around him, came to a halt, and a smiling woman asked him what he wanted. 'To buy...' said Luzhin, continuing to look around. At this point he caught sight of a wax bust and pointed to it with his cane (an unexpected move, a magnificent move). 'That's not for sale,' said the woman.

'Twenty marks,' said Luzhin and took out his pocketbook. 'You want to buy that dummy?' asked the woman unbelievingly, 